D. Interdisciplinary Connections: The RSVP-CPG framework is not presented as an isolated neurodynamical theory but rather intersects with various domains across cognitive science, evolutionary biology, and applied research. Several connections are sketched: language as rhythmic entrainment, social cognition and collective gait, learning and memory as rhythm stabilization, evolutionary biology and comparative gait, and applied connections in human-computer interaction, education, and clinical therapy.

The RSVP-CPG framework offers a unique perspective on consciousness by emphasizing cortical cycles' role in structuring perception and action over time, unifying multiple aspects of cognition under the concept of a "gait." It aims to provide a synthesis across various domains of study.


