This paper proposes a unified mathematical and neurobiological framework to understand how cortical computation emerges from local nonlinear transformations and global geometric dynamics. The central idea is to model cortical columns as amplistwistors, nonlinear operators acting on RSVP (Relativistic Scalar Vector Plenum) fields that represent semantic density, inferential flow, and uncertainty, respectively.

1. Mathematical Foundation:
   - RSVP: A non-linear system of coupled partial differential equations (PDEs) describing the evolution of semantic fields across a spatial manifold. This system incorporates diﬀusion, nonlinear coupling, and entropy regulation, providing a biologically plausible model of cortical ﬁelds supporting inference, integration, and uncertainty reduction.

2. Cortical Columns as Amplistwistors:
