### Emergent Structures

Title: Emergent Structures and Control in Neural, Cosmic, and Artificial Intelligence Systems via RSVP and TARTAN

This research paper proposes a unified field-theoretic framework to understand emergent structures and control mechanisms across neural, cosmic, and artificial intelligence systems. The core of this framework is the Relativistic Scalar Vector Plenum (RSVP) model, complemented by its recursive extension, Trajectory-Aware Recursive Tiling with Annotated Noise (TARTAN).

The RSVP framework models emergent phenomena through three fundamental fields: a scalar field Φ(x, t), representing semantic density or neural activation strength; a vector field ⃗v(x, t), capturing information flow; and an entropy field S(x, t), measuring ambiguity. These fields are interconnected via nonlinear coupling terms that introduce complex dynamics.

