This monograph introduces a unique interpretation of Arkady and Boris Strugatsky's "The Doomed City" using the Relativistic Scalar-Vector Plenum (RSVP) theory—a field-theoretic model of entropy dynamics. The RSVP framework conceptualizes physical and informational systems as coupled scalar (Φ) and vector (v) fields evolving toward an entropic ground state, providing a novel lens through which to analyze the narrative.

